ce:section.ce:para:
Carbon nanostructures have been extensively studied due to their excellent physical and properties, and numerous applications [1]. Graphite is one of the well-known carbon based materials. Because of its layered structure, graphite can readily intercalated by using different materials such as acids [2,3], alkali metals [4], FeCl3 
                     [5,6], organic solvent and organic molecules [7–10]. By packing a flat monolayer of carbon atoms tightly into a two-dimensional (2D) honeycomb lattice, graphene is going to be made. Graphene can be considered as a fundamental building block for graphitic materials of all other important allotropes [11] (Scheme 1
                     ).
